casebody.data:
In re Eric A. JOHNSON, Huei-Hsiung Yan, Beril Geldiay-Tuncer, William T. Hall, David Schreiber, and Kwok Ho (Real Party in Interest Biotechnology, Inc.). No. 04-1360. United States Court of Appeals, Federal Circuit. Oct. 20, 2004.

ON MOTION

NEWMAN, Circuit Judge.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the parties’ joint motion to remand the case to the United States Patent and Trademark Office for further proceedings,

IT IS ORDERED THAT:

(1) The motion is granted.

(2) Each side shall bear its own costs.
